        <h1 style="line-height: 26px !important;">Hydraulisc Cookies Policy</h1>
        <hr>
        <div class="maincontent">
            <div>
                <div>
                    <span>
                        <p><i>We have updated our Cookie Policiy. This updated document is effective as of March 6th, 2026.</i></p>
                    </span>
                </div>
                <span>
                    <br>
                    <div>
                        <div>
                            <p>Cookies help us provide, protect and improve The Hydraulisc Network Products, mainly by providing a safer experience and reinforcing client-side authentication verification. The cookies that we use include persistent cookies, which stay in your browser until they expire or you delete them. The cookies that we  may change over time as we improve and update The Hydraulisc Network Products, we typically use them for the following purposes:</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <details style="cursor: default;">
                                <summary>Authentication</summary>
                                <hr>
                                <ul>
                                    <li style="margin-top: auto;">We use cookies to verify your account and determine when you're logged in so that we can make it easier for you to access The Hydraulisc Network Products and show you the appropriate experience and features.</li>
                                    <p>For example: We use cookies to keep you logged in as you navigate between Hydraulisc Pages. Cookies also help us remember your browser so you don't have to keep logging in to Hydraulisc and so you can more easily log in to Hydraulisc via third-party apps and websites. For example, we use the "connect.sid" and "cookiesAccepted" cookies, which have a rolling lifespan of 2 days.</p>
                                </ul>
                            </details>
                            <details style="cursor: default;">
                                <summary>Security, product integrity, insights, analytics and measurements</summary>
                                <hr>
                                <ul>
                                    <li style="margin-top: auto;">We use cookies to help us keep your account, data and The Hydraulisc Network Products safe and secure.</li>
                                    <p>For example: Cookies can help us identify and impose additional security measures when someone may be attempting to access a Hydraulisc account without authorisation, for instance, by rapidly guessing different passwords.</p>
                                    <li>We use cookies to provide you with the best experience possible.</li>
                                    <p>For example: Cookies help us route traffic between servers and understand how quickly The Hydraulisc Network Products load for different people. Cookies also help us record your theme selection, and know whether you've enabled high-contrast mode, so that we can render our sites and apps correctly. For example, we set the "theme" and "customTheme" cookies, each with a rolling lifespan of two days, for purposes including to deliver an optimal experience for your chosen theme.</p>
                                    <li>We use cookies to better understand how people use The Hydraulisc Network Products so that we can improve them.</li>
                                    <p>For example: Cookies can help us understand how people use the Hydraulisc service, analyse which parts of our Products people find most useful and engaging, and identify features that could be improved.</p>
                                    <li>Cookies also allow us to provide insights about the people who use The Hydraulisc Network Products, as well as the people who interact with the ads, and the businesses that use The Hydraulisc Network Products.</li>
                                    <p>For example: We use cookies to help businesses understand the number of people who like their Hydraulisc Posts or interacted with their advertisement.</p>
                                </ul>
                            </details>
                        </div>
                        <br>
